The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 05 March is 40,470 (4,684.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 28 February, there were 494 new confirmed cases (57.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 21 February, there were 737 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 33% (243 fewer cases).
